-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"962696b1-43ad-5f51-8f00-68d3a4dda8dd","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"1443b3b6-a17c-52cb-9732-24a58e05f435","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"6f26253b-1a92-5f27-8fc7-01f17834ec23","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"6b936218-a18e-529e-88b7-3bcf3f811c11","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"8e453b92-23b4-5cad-95b6-9c677c0269a2","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"39990bfd-9566-5252-b7b1-ecb7a6fc4541","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"a2fc91ae-fac9-5505-928a-deaebdf150c8","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Management"},"subChapters":[{"id":"234a2a64-14fc-5641-a0cd-137d3bbaa252","slug":"management-referral","fullItemName":"Management (referral)","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field d27fd5dd-7d21-4523-baf8-a5158a774b78 --><h3>How should I manage a baby or child who has a suspected cataract?</h3><!-- end field d27fd5dd-7d21-4523-baf8-a5158a774b78 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 6f6622b6-d70e-4e98-86d4-073b288bc62d --><!-- begin field 797436c4-342d-4007-8647-59b9b69b07b7 --><ul><li>Urgently refer any baby or child with a <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/diagnosis/diagnosis-child/\">suspected cataract</a> to an ophthalmologist.<ul><li>Same day telephone referral to a paediatric ophthalmologist is warranted if examination for the red reflex shows:<ul><li>The presence of an opacity in the red reflex.</li><li>The absence of any reflex.</li><li>A white pupillary reflex (leukocoria).</li></ul></li><li>Urgent written referral to the ophthalmologist is recommended if the examination shows:<ul><li>Inequality in colour, intensity, or clarity of the reflection.</li><li>No detectable abnormality but a parent or carer describes a history suspicious of leukocoria (white pupil) on observation or in a photograph (recognising, however, that the most common cause of a white pupil in flash photography is reflection from the optic disc of the in-turning eye when fixation is off-axis to the camera).</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><strong>Ensure assessment by a paediatrician has been carried out </strong>for underlying causes of congenital cataract.<ul><li>This is likely to be arranged by the ophthalmologist following the urgent initial referral.</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 797436c4-342d-4007-8647-59b9b69b07b7 --><!-- end item 6f6622b6-d70e-4e98-86d4-073b288bc62d -->","subChapters":[{"id":"bbd8c62c-a1b5-5b93-835f-b27a054e343e","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-7ba","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":4,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 9fd9b653-36ed-44bb-a699-f1a679c9509a --><h4>Basis for recommendation</h4><!-- end field 9fd9b653-36ed-44bb-a699-f1a679c9509a -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 7ba3a3ba-f8ca-4008-a756-5f849bd06476 --><!-- begin field 2034c929-1216-45c5-a02e-e1a9a827afb4 --><p>These recommendations are based on expert opinion in narrative reviews <em>Congenital cataract</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/references/\">Russell et al, 2011</a>] and <em>Paediatric cataract: challenges and future direction</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/references/\">Medsinge and Nischal, 2015</a>], and what CKS consider good clinical practice.</p><!-- end field 2034c929-1216-45c5-a02e-e1a9a827afb4 --><!-- end item 7ba3a3ba-f8ca-4008-a756-5f849bd06476 -->","subChapters":[]}]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}